    <p>
        <term>Key Takeaway.</term>
    </p>
    <p>
        When data is organized into class intervals, each interval is represented by its <term><em>mid-point</em></term>, which is the average of the <em>lower</em> and <em>upper</em> boundaries of that class.
    </p>
    <p>
        Mid-point can be denoted as;
        <me>
            \bar{X} = \frac{\text{upper limit + lower limit}}{2}
        </me>        
    </p>
    <p>
        <me>
            \text{Mean} = \frac{\text{sum of all values}}{\text{total frequency}}
        </me>        
    </p>
    <p>
        Mean is represented by the symbol <m>\bar{X}</m>, read as <m>X</m> bar.
    </p>
    <p>
        Thus,
        <me>
            \bar{X} = \frac{\sum{fx}}{\sum{f}}
        </me>        
    </p>
    <p>
        The symbol <m>\sum</m>(sigma) means "sum of" and is used to indicate that you should add up all the values in the specified range.
    </p>
